AGI - Latium Tar suspends the call for 31 bathing concessions on the Roman coast. The fifth section of the Administrative Court of Lazio has accepted the appeal submitted by some bathers against Rome Capital and the Demanio Agency for the annulment, after granting appropriate precautionary measures, of the public notice of 14 February 2025 for the entrustment of 31 concessions of marine property of the coast of Rome Capital for tourist and recreational purposes, the management determination with which has been called the general council
&nbsp;
The Tar accepted the precautionary application and suspended the race fixing the hearing on 14 October 2025.
<h2>Assessore Zevi: bathing season 2025</h2>
"We note the decision of the Tar del Lazio, which suspended the call for the custody of 31 bathing concessions in Ostia, referring the discussion of the merit to 14 October 2025, but we consider it indispensable to proceed with the appeal to the State Council; we remain firm on the solidity of the values and principles underlying the published bands." Tobia Zevi, a city councillor for the patrimony and housing policies of Rome Capital, says this, ensuring that "the bathing season 2025> will be guaranteed to benefit from an equipped and safe bathing."
&nbsp;
The suspensive of the Tar, exited a few hours, explains a note of the Municipality of Rome, "does not cancel the race but temporarily stops the iter, highlighting nodes to dissolve linked to the application of national and regional regulations. The central one, in particular, concerns the absence of the Sandstone Use Plan (Pua), which under regional law imposes on the Administration the indication of maximum annual duration races, while the national standard provides a duration of between five to a maximum of twenty years".
&nbsp;
"A decision by the State Council is fundamental to understand whether national legislation prevails on the regional one and if, therefore, it is possible to proceed with multiannual competitions even in the absence of the Pua; the objective of the Administration is to guarantee transparency, legality and the correct use of the maritime demanio, in accordance with the rules in force. We respect any pronunciation, but we believe that our approach is respectful of the legislation and principles enshrined in the new law and - Zevi concludes - we firmly defend the innovation related to royalty as an opportunity of real valorisation of the coast". &nbsp;

